01:04:03.000 --> 01:04:04.000
So let's study objectively what we can.

01:04:05.000 --> 01:04:06.000
Behavior.

01:04:07.000 --> 01:04:08.000
When we get to the psyche,

01:04:08.000 --> 01:04:09.000
so that we can study it objectively,

01:04:10.000 --> 01:04:11.000
measure it,

01:04:12.000 --> 01:04:13.000
assess it,

01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:15.000
indicate it,

01:04:16.000 --> 01:04:17.000
then we will study it

01:04:18.000 --> 01:04:19.000
using scientific methods.

01:04:20.000 --> 01:04:21.000
The ideal for behaviorists

01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:23.000
has always been the accuracy of consciousness,

01:04:24.000 --> 01:04:25.000
physics.

01:04:26.000 --> 01:04:27.000
No matter what you know,

01:04:28.000 --> 01:04:29.000
no matter what you don't know,

01:04:30.000 --> 01:04:31.000
if you conduct any physical experiment,

01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:33.000
and you conduct it

01:04:34.000 --> 01:04:35.000
with the same initial data,

01:04:36.000 --> 01:04:37.000
you will always get

01:04:38.000 --> 01:04:39.000
the same result.

01:04:40.000 --> 01:04:41.000
If you didn't get the same result,

01:04:42.000 --> 01:04:43.000
then you made a mistake somewhere.

01:04:44.000 --> 01:04:45.000
And you need to find this mistake.

01:04:46.000 --> 01:04:48.000
Behaviorists liked this very much.

01:04:49.000 --> 01:04:50.000
No matter what,

01:04:51.000 --> 01:04:52.000
there is an incentive,

01:04:53.000 --> 01:04:54.000
there is a reaction.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:56.000
However,

01:04:57.000 --> 01:04:58.000
in the middle of the last century

01:04:59.000 --> 01:05:00.000
it became necessary

01:05:01.000 --> 01:05:02.000
for the same behaviorists

01:05:03.000 --> 01:05:04.000
to address

01:05:05.000 --> 01:05:06.000
the human psyche.

01:05:06.000 --> 01:05:07.000
And a paradoxical direction

01:05:08.000 --> 01:05:09.000
arises.

01:05:10.000 --> 01:05:11.000
Cognitive-behavioral.

01:05:12.000 --> 01:05:13.000
It seems to be an incompatible function.

01:05:14.000 --> 01:05:15.000
Behaviorist of behavior,

01:05:16.000 --> 01:05:17.000
cognition,

01:05:18.000 --> 01:05:19.000
is the psyche.

01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:21.000
And here the negative behaviorist

01:05:22.000 --> 01:05:23.000
of the psyche

01:05:24.000 --> 01:05:25.000
is connected.

01:05:26.000 --> 01:05:27.000
And accordingly,

01:05:28.000 --> 01:05:29.000
a direction appears

01:05:30.000 --> 01:05:31.000
that tries to measure

01:05:32.000 --> 01:05:33.000
our cognitive moments

01:05:34.000 --> 01:05:35.000
by behavioral methods.

01:05:36.000 --> 01:05:37.000
And what is introduced

01:05:38.000 --> 01:05:39.000
is the so-called internal variables.

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:41.000
What you see on the slide.

01:05:42.000 --> 01:05:43.000
External stimuli

01:05:44.000 --> 01:05:45.000
affect

01:05:46.000 --> 01:05:47.000
a person,

01:05:48.000 --> 01:05:49.000
a monkey,

01:05:50.000 --> 01:05:51.000
a higher animal.

01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:53.000
In this case, behaviorists

01:05:54.000 --> 01:05:55.000
consider the higher animals

01:05:56.000 --> 01:05:57.000
which have a certain

01:05:58.000 --> 01:05:59.000
psychological way of processing reality.

01:06:00.000 --> 01:06:01.000
Stimuli affect this psyche.

01:06:02.000 --> 01:06:03.000
And then from this psyche,

01:06:04.000 --> 01:06:05.000
depending on

01:06:06.000 --> 01:06:07.000
the processing of this stimulus,

01:06:08.000 --> 01:06:09.000
a reaction appears.

01:06:10.000 --> 01:06:11.000
So,

01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:13.000
the stimulus,

01:06:14.000 --> 01:06:15.000
the internal variables,

01:06:16.000 --> 01:06:17.000
they got the name

01:06:18.000 --> 01:06:19.000
of the cognitive map

01:06:20.000 --> 01:06:21.000
after Tolman.

01:06:22.000 --> 01:06:23.000
And only then the reaction.

01:06:24.000 --> 01:06:25.000
Behavior.

01:06:26.000 --> 01:06:27.000
The difference...

01:06:28.000 --> 01:06:29.000
What is the difference from the previous scheme?

01:06:30.000 --> 01:06:31.000
The difference is fundamental.

01:06:32.000 --> 01:06:33.000
Before, we change only the stimuli

01:06:34.000 --> 01:06:35.000
and get behavior.

01:06:36.000 --> 01:06:37.000
There was a purely mechanical scheme.

01:06:38.000 --> 01:06:39.000
I increased the power of the stimulus,

01:06:40.000 --> 01:06:41.000
I decreased the power of the stimulus,

01:06:42.000 --> 01:06:43.000
I added, increased,

01:06:44.000 --> 01:06:45.000
I got an increase,

01:06:46.000 --> 01:06:47.000
a decrease in the reaction.

01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:49.000
Direct proportionality,

01:06:50.000 --> 01:06:51.000
direct opposite.

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:53.000
Now the situation changes.

01:06:54.000 --> 01:06:55.000
There are stimuli,

01:06:56.000 --> 01:06:57.000
all the same,

01:06:58.000 --> 01:06:59.000
the most objective stimuli.

01:07:00.000 --> 01:07:01.000
They affect the human psyche.

01:07:02.000 --> 01:07:03.000
And the psyche is different for everyone.

01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:05.000
We have different experiences,

01:07:06.000 --> 01:07:07.000
we have different coordination.

01:07:08.000 --> 01:07:09.000
And these stimuli

01:07:10.000 --> 01:07:11.000
affect

01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:13.000
the psyche

01:07:14.000 --> 01:07:15.000
of an animal.

01:07:16.000 --> 01:07:17.000
And already depending on

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:19.000
how this psyche

01:07:20.000 --> 01:07:21.000
evaluates these stimuli,

01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:23.000
depending on its experience,

01:07:24.000 --> 01:07:25.000
depending on its memory,

01:07:26.000 --> 01:07:27.000
depending on its attention,

01:07:28.000 --> 01:07:29.000
depending on how these stimuli were used,

01:07:30.000 --> 01:07:31.000
depending on those

01:07:32.000 --> 01:07:33.000
psychological images

01:07:34.000 --> 01:07:35.000
that the person had,

01:07:36.000 --> 01:07:37.000
depending on the human thinking,

01:07:38.000 --> 01:07:39.000
I will have

01:07:40.000 --> 01:07:41.000
a certain reaction.

01:07:42.000 --> 01:07:43.000
The simplest example is

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:45.000
an experienced manager

01:07:46.000 --> 01:07:47.000
and a beginner.

01:07:48.000 --> 01:07:49.000
They get

01:07:50.000 --> 01:07:51.000
the same initial data.

01:07:52.000 --> 01:07:53.000
But if a beginner

01:07:54.000 --> 01:07:55.000
starts acting

01:07:56.000 --> 01:07:57.000
according to the general patterns

01:07:58.000 --> 01:07:59.000
that he was taught,

01:08:00.000 --> 01:08:01.000
then the experienced manager

01:08:02.000 --> 01:08:03.000
already knows

01:08:03.000 --> 01:08:04.000
where something will work,

01:08:05.000 --> 01:08:06.000
where something will not work.

01:08:07.000 --> 01:08:08.000
The experienced manager already knows

01:08:09.000 --> 01:08:10.000
pointless ways

01:08:11.000 --> 01:08:12.000
that will not lead to

01:08:13.000 --> 01:08:14.000
the desired result.

01:08:15.000 --> 01:08:16.000
And accordingly,

01:08:17.000 --> 01:08:18.000
he saves time

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:20.000
by not doing these actions.

01:08:21.000 --> 01:08:22.000
Therefore,

01:08:23.000 --> 01:08:24.000
he will achieve the result

01:08:25.000 --> 01:08:26.000
incomparably faster than a beginner.

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:28.000
And since he achieved the result quickly,

01:08:29.000 --> 01:08:30.000
he has a certain

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:31.000
time to do

01:08:32.000 --> 01:08:33.000
certain sales,

01:08:34.000 --> 01:08:35.000
to provide certain services

01:08:36.000 --> 01:08:37.000
during a certain time interval.

01:08:38.000 --> 01:08:39.000
This is what the inner variables have.

01:08:40.000 --> 01:08:41.000
In fact, this is an experience,

01:08:42.000 --> 01:08:43.000
the experience that is acquired

01:08:44.000 --> 01:08:45.000
by an animal and a human

01:08:46.000 --> 01:08:47.000
based on the fact

01:08:48.000 --> 01:08:49.000
that they take part

01:08:50.000 --> 01:08:51.000
in different kinds of actions,

01:08:52.000 --> 01:08:53.000
different kinds of events.

01:08:54.000 --> 01:08:55.000
When an animal

01:08:56.000 --> 01:08:57.000
is not a human,

01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:58.000
it is a human.

01:08:59.000 --> 01:09:00.000
When we talk about

01:09:01.000 --> 01:09:02.000
the cognitive behavioral direction,

01:09:03.000 --> 01:09:04.000
it is primarily associated

01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:06.000
with Albert Bandura

01:09:07.000 --> 01:09:08.000
and Julian Rotter.

01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Of course, there were other researchers,

01:09:11.000 --> 01:09:12.000
but since our task

01:09:13.000 --> 01:09:14.000
is to get acquainted

01:09:15.000 --> 01:09:16.000
with the main,

01:09:17.000 --> 01:09:18.000
key directions,

01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:20.000
the key figures here

01:09:21.000 --> 01:09:22.000
are these two figures,

01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:24.000
Bandura and Rotter.

01:09:25.000 --> 01:09:26.000
As for Albert Bandura,

01:09:27.000 --> 01:09:28.000
his basic idea

01:09:29.000 --> 01:09:30.000
that he implemented

01:09:31.000 --> 01:09:32.000
was that

01:09:33.000 --> 01:09:34.000
he proposed

01:09:35.000 --> 01:09:36.000
to build,

01:09:37.000 --> 01:09:38.000
to analyze

01:09:39.000 --> 01:09:40.000
learning from the point of view

01:09:41.000 --> 01:09:42.000
of observation.

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:44.000
What does a person do?

01:09:45.000 --> 01:09:46.000
What does a child do?

01:09:47.000 --> 01:09:48.000
What does a long-sighted manager

01:09:49.000 --> 01:09:50.000
who came to work do?

01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:52.000
He starts to look

01:09:53.000 --> 01:09:54.000
at the behavior of other people

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:56.000
who do not have

01:09:57.000 --> 01:09:58.000
similar functions,

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:00.000
who perform

01:10:01.000 --> 01:10:02.000
similar actions,

01:10:03.000 --> 01:10:04.000
and tries to

01:10:05.000 --> 01:10:06.000
record

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:08.000
the key elements

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:10.000
of their behavior

01:10:11.000 --> 01:10:12.000
that make them successful.

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:14.000
If I have recorded

01:10:15.000 --> 01:10:16.000
these elements of behavior,

01:10:17.000 --> 01:10:18.000
then I start

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:20.000
to reproduce

01:10:21.000 --> 01:10:22.000
this behavior.

01:10:23.000 --> 01:10:24.000
And if I have modeled

01:10:25.000 --> 01:10:26.000
the behavior

01:10:27.000 --> 01:10:28.000
of a person

01:10:29.000 --> 01:10:30.000
in a way

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:32.000
that I can

01:10:33.000 --> 01:10:34.000
do it,

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:36.000
then I can

01:10:37.000 --> 01:10:38.000
achieve the desired result.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:40.000
If I have missed

01:10:41.000 --> 01:10:42.000
some elements,

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:44.000
then I can

01:10:45.000 --> 01:10:46.000
achieve the desired result,

01:10:47.000 --> 01:10:48.000
but not so fast,

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:50.000
not so good,

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:52.000
or I will be disappointed

01:10:53.000 --> 01:10:54.000
and will consider

01:10:55.000 --> 01:10:56.000
that what I do

01:10:57.000 --> 01:10:58.000
is inappropriate

01:10:59.000 --> 01:11:00.000
for community

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:02.000
and the society.

01:11:03.000 --> 01:11:04.000
If I have

01:11:05.000 --> 01:11:06.000
demonstrated

01:11:08.000 --> 01:11:09.000
a poor skill

01:11:11.000 --> 01:11:12.000
to someone

01:11:13.000 --> 01:11:14.240
then I'm

01:11:15.000 --> 01:11:16.000
not a good person.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:18.000
If I have

01:11:19.000 --> 01:11:20.000
done

01:11:21.000 --> 01:11:22.000
my best

01:11:23.000 --> 01:11:24.000
for my country,

01:11:25.000 --> 01:11:26.000
my community,

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:28.000
this black box

01:11:29.000 --> 01:11:30.000
starts to behave.

01:11:31.000 --> 01:11:32.000
It's a passive object

01:11:33.000 --> 01:11:34.000
with an external influence

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:36.000
and reaction.

01:11:37.000 --> 01:11:38.000
Bandoora makes a completely different situation.

01:11:39.000 --> 01:11:40.000
Bandoora from a human

01:11:41.000 --> 01:11:42.000
makes an active,

01:11:43.000 --> 01:11:44.000
acting being.

01:11:46.000 --> 01:11:47.000
Because

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:49.000
these inner variables

01:11:50.000 --> 01:11:51.000
these cognitive maps

01:11:52.000 --> 01:11:53.000
are my observations.

01:11:53.000 --> 01:11:54.000
I'm stimulated.

01:11:55.000 --> 01:11:56.000
I activate my memory.

01:11:57.000 --> 01:11:58.000
I activate my existing experience.

01:11:59.000 --> 01:12:00.000
I activate my systematic observation.

01:12:01.000 --> 01:12:02.000
And I try to get the desired result.

01:12:03.000 --> 01:12:04.000
If I don't get the result

01:12:05.000 --> 01:12:06.000
or if I don't get the result

01:12:07.000 --> 01:12:08.000
that I want

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:10.000
then I myself

01:12:11.000 --> 01:12:12.000
without changing my behavior

01:12:13.000 --> 01:12:14.000
I'm not a human being.

